Messi is an Argentine professional footballer widely regarded as one of the greatest players in the history of the sport.
Born on June 24, 1987, in Rosario, Argentina, he overcame a childhood growth hormone deficiency before joining Barcelona's youth academy at the age of 13.
During his legendary career with FC Barcelona, he won numerous domestic and international titles, including multiple UEFA Champions League and La Liga trophies, while becoming the club's all-time leading scorer.
Messi has also played for Paris Saint-Germain and currently plays for Inter Miami.
Internationally, he led Argentina to victory in the 2022 FIFA World Cup and has won multiple Copa América titles.
Known for his extraordinary dribbling, vision, passing, finishing, and playmaking ability, Messi has won a record eight Ballon d'Or awards and is celebrated by fans and experts as one of football's greatest-ever players